main event: A radar indicated an object initially heading ENE at approx. 2000 mph, then slowed to approx. 600 mph. Radar scope indicated two bright oval objects, one larger than the other.
interesting points: The objects were observed until they disappeared from radar scope.
Rapid movement, size and behavior indicated the objects were probably intelligently controlled.
The case could not be satisfactorily explained and was evaluated as a MINOR CASE.
